462
00:17:18,624 --> 00:17:19,136
DANIEL: Ah, a bet?

463
00:17:19,136 --> 00:17:20,400
JAEWON: A gift card bet?

464
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,344
DANIEL: Deal!

465
00:17:21,966 --> 00:17:23,033
(Sneaky exit)
HAMIN: Just you two.

466
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:24,666
JAEWON: Ah, we should do this together.

467
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:25,833
(Inexperienced)
HAMIN: I haven't done it, but

468
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:26,866
HAMIN: I need to try to know.

469
00:17:26,866 --> 00:17:28,400
(Six years ago)
JAEWON: My last time was fifth grade.

470
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:30,720
HAMIN: What, then why do you say you're good?

471
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:33,666
JAEWON: We have CHARLIE, who's good at sports.

472
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:34,912
(Climbing hopeful CHARLIE)
DANIEL: CHARLIE seems like he'll do well.

473
00:17:34,912 --> 00:17:36,500
- JAEWON: Because he is light.
- DANIEL: I think you'd be good at hanging.

474
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:37,400
HAMIN: Have you tried it?

475
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,300
CHARLIE: I've tried it.

476
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,400
HAMIN: Raise your hand then.

477
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,700
CHARLIE: I just did it recently.

478
00:17:41,933 --> 00:17:42,688
(CHARLIE feeling awkward as friends raise hands)
JAEWON: I've tried it.

479
00:17:43,616 --> 00:17:44,620
(Late hand raise)
JAEWON: I'm good at climbing.

480
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:45,400
- TRAINEE: Are you good at it?
- DANIEL: You?

481
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:47,433
HAMIN: Raise confidently, confidently!!

482
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,088
- DANIEL: Right
- HAMIN: Right.

483
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:52,000
(Everyone has tried except HAMIN and HARUTA)
STAFF: Except HAMIN and HARUTA, everyone's done it.

484
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:53,466
HAMIN: But, what about the others?

485
00:17:53,466 --> 00:17:54,933
HAMIN: They probably did it when they were younger.

486
00:17:55,633 --> 00:17:57,533
HAMIN: Isn't it all just about the same?

487
00:17:57,666 --> 00:17:58,766
- DANIEL: Not really.
- JAEWON: Are we competing directly?

488
00:17:58,766 --> 00:18:00,166
DANIEL: Everything else is quite similar!

489
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:01,696
DANIEL: It's just DANIEL here alone.

490
00:18:01,696 --> 00:18:02,700
CHARLIE: Wow!

491
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:03,900
- HARUTA: Got it.
- JAEWON: Really?

492
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,566
(Will DANIEL be at the top alone?)
DANIEL: Nice reaction.

493
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:10,300
(WONHA~JANNI's experiential learning
chosen by vote: climbing)

494
00:18:12,608 --> 00:18:13,920
(10 meters high, the height of a 3 to 4 story building)
TRAINEE: That looks tough.

495
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:16,533
JAEWON: Wow, it's high!

496
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:19,333
DANIEL: Yeah, it's low!

497
00:18:19,866 --> 00:18:20,900
HARUTA: I'm feeling nervous.

498
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,066
HARUTA: Because I haven't tried it.

499
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,500
HARUTA: I feel like I won't be able to do it.

500
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,900
HAMIN: Well, it's easier than I thought.

501
00:18:25,024 --> 00:18:26,500
HARUTA: I don't have any muscle.

502
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,613
HAMIN: But it doesn't matter.

503
00:18:27,613 --> 00:18:28,733
HARUTA: Really?

504
00:18:28,928 --> 00:18:32,033
(1. Improving physical strength)

505
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,400
HAMIN: I feel like I'm going to die if I look down.

506
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,904
HAMIN: Just a moment.

507
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:37,933
DANIEL: Why are you so scared?

508
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:40,433
(2. Building courage)

509
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:41,386
JAEWON: Is this gray?

510
00:18:41,386 --> 00:18:42,048
DANIEL: Yeah.

511
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,900
HARUTA: Right there, right there.

512
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,150
JAEWON: This one, this one?

513
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:46,400
TRAINEE: Yeah, right, right.

514
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,936
(It's a creative experience activity)
DANIEL: Where to lay the hand?

515
00:18:47,936 --> 00:18:48,866
(where you can expect cooperation
and communication skills)

516
00:18:48,866 --> 00:18:50,496
(10m climb practice starts first)

517
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:52,000
CHARLIE: HAMIN. Let's go.

518
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,400
HAMIN: Why me first?

519
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,200
(The first one is HAMIN)

520
00:18:55,264 --> 00:18:56,733
(Ahem)

521
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:59,366
(Surprised
As soon as the harness is hooked, the rope tightens)

522
00:18:59,366 --> 00:19:01,280
DANIEL: It's the first time I've seen HAMIN
overreacting like that.

523
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:03,296
HAMIN: I'm really scared.

524
00:19:04,266 --> 00:19:07,000
(HAMIN starts climbing the 10m)

525
00:19:07,136 --> 00:19:09,900
(We filmed this with safety in mind)
TRAINEE: Some rather large ones.

526
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,433
HARUTA: I don't think I can do it.

527
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:13,700
(Suddenly climbing to twice the height)

528
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:14,528
DANIEL: Come down now.

529
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:15,424
TRAINEE: How far are we going?

530
00:19:15,968 --> 00:19:16,800
HAMIN: No? I'm going further.

531
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,633
(Adventurous spirit +10)

532
00:19:19,072 --> 00:19:20,266
HAMIN: Oh! Oh!

533
00:19:20,266 --> 00:19:21,666
(Courage -10)

534
00:19:22,528 --> 00:19:24,192
HAMIN: I feel like I'm going to die if I look down.

535
00:19:24,192 --> 00:19:25,344
HAMIN: Just a moment.

536
00:19:25,966 --> 00:19:27,456
DANIEL: Why are you so scared?

537
00:19:27,936 --> 00:19:30,080
(Courage -10)

538
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:31,800
HARUTA: Look, look!

539
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:32,813
HAMIN: No, I can't.

540
00:19:32,966 --> 00:19:34,166
(Summoning courage to turn the head)
HAMIN: No!

541
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:35,566
(Courage +2)

542
00:19:37,766 --> 00:19:38,866
HAMIN: How do I go down?

543
00:19:39,966 --> 00:19:43,300
(Boldly letting go
You have to trust the rope with your body)

544
00:19:43,552 --> 00:19:44,544
DANIEL: You need to drop.

545
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,166
(Remarkably climbed quite high)

546
00:19:47,616 --> 00:19:49,728
(Eye shock)

547
00:19:49,966 --> 00:19:51,136
DANIEL: HAMIN, look here!

548
00:19:51,136 --> 00:19:52,352
(The older brother is too busy taking commemorative
photos to know his younger sibling's feelings)

549
00:19:52,352 --> 00:19:52,866
DANIEL: Kimchi!

550
00:19:52,866 --> 00:19:54,566
HARUTA: You've got to look at the camera. The camera.

551
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:57,866
(No mood for that)
HAMIN: Ugh!

552
00:19:58,112 --> 00:19:59,424
TRAINEE: Until the end, until the end!

553
00:19:59,424 --> 00:20:01,056
(Going down is a problem for later,
but HAMIN keeps going till the end)

554
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,800
DANIEL: Why aren't you using your feet?

555
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,133
HARUTA: It's all going with muscle.

556
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,760
(Forearm strength +30)
TRAINEE: Doing everything with the arms?

557
00:20:06,066 --> 00:20:07,766
(Indeed, solving everything with muscle)
TRAINEE: All with muscle.

558
00:20:08,448 --> 00:20:10,133
(HAMIN stands at the top of 10m)
TRAINEE: Come down now.

559
00:20:10,566 --> 00:20:11,392
HAMIN: Can't I not jump?

560
00:20:11,392 --> 00:20:12,480
TRAINEE: No, you have to jump.

561
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,016
HAMIN: I don't think I can jump, really!

562
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:16,600
HAMIN: Is there any way not to jump?

563
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:19,566
STAFF: It might be a bit embarrassing.

564
00:20:19,566 --> 00:20:21,440
DANIEL: You need to maintain your image.

565
00:20:21,766 --> 00:20:22,966
(Courage -10)
HAMIN: Yeah, but I'm really scared.

566
00:20:22,966 --> 00:20:24,300
JAEWON: Come on!

567
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,824
(While HAMIN is stuck with a timid image)
TRAINEE: You have to manage your image.

568
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:31,300
(Meanwhile, the bus that Class '90 got on)

569
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:36,766
(Suddenly, the ocean near Gyeongju comes into view)

570
00:20:37,568 --> 00:20:39,296
JUSTIN: Wow!

571
00:20:40,736 --> 00:20:41,760
TRAINEE: Wow!

572
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,392
(Sea view stretching beside the bus)
TRAINEE: It's the sea!

573
00:20:43,392 --> 00:20:44,033
TRAINEE: It's the sea!

574
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:46,100
WOOLIN: Wow, there are so many birds on that island!

575
00:20:47,488 --> 00:20:49,504
(Among them, a rocky island
with a lot of birds stands out)

576
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:53,000
(Tomb of King Munmu)
STAFF: Our first school field trip location is

577
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,633
STAFF: the Tomb of King Munmu.

578
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:57,766
HYUNJUN: Wow, I'm so excited!

579
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,119
JUSTIN: Woah!

580
00:20:59,119 --> 00:21:00,399
KASSHO: Wow, a beach!

581
00:21:00,832 --> 00:21:01,786
TRAINEE: Shall we go?

582
00:21:01,799 --> 00:21:02,784
(The first school field trip destination)
TRAINEE: Let's go.

583
00:21:02,912 --> 00:21:04,128
(located by the seaside)
TRAINEE: Let's go.

584
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:07,099
(Current location)

585
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:09,766
(Echoing)
HYUNJUN: Gyeongju, we arrived!

586
00:21:09,856 --> 00:21:10,784
WOOLIN: Come on, come on!

587
00:21:11,399 --> 00:21:12,064
(High schoolers excited by the outdoor breeze)
JUSTIN: Shall we go?

588
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:12,864
WOOLIN: Let's go!

589
00:21:12,864 --> 00:21:13,952
KASSHO: Let's go!

590
00:21:14,366 --> 00:21:16,466
NICHOLAS: Where are we exactly?

591
00:21:16,466 --> 00:21:18,399
NICHOLAS: HYUNJUN, where is this place?

592
00:21:18,399 --> 00:21:20,199
HYUNJUN: We are currently

593
00:21:20,199 --> 00:21:22,333
HYUNJUN: near Tomb of King Munmu.

594
00:21:22,666 --> 00:21:23,899
NICHOLAS: Close to the Tomb of King Munmu?

595
00:21:23,899 --> 00:21:24,750
HYUNJUN: It's the sea.

596
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:25,600
NICHOLAS: Sea.

597
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:29,024
(The Tomb of King Munmu is somewhere along this coastline)
NICHOLAS: We've arrived at the seaside.

598
00:21:29,536 --> 00:21:30,566
HYUNJUN: Wow, the sound.

599
00:21:32,899 --> 00:21:35,366
WOOLIN: Wow, it's really the sea. Oh, it's amazing!

600
00:21:35,433 --> 00:21:36,064
KASSHO: It feels great.

601
00:21:36,064 --> 00:21:36,640
(Excitement)
WOOLIN: It's been a long time

602
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,440
WOOLIN: since I've been to the ocean.

603
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:38,733
STAFF: Okay, students.

604
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:41,366
STAFF: What you're seeing right now in front of you is

605
00:21:41,699 --> 00:21:43,533
STAFF: the tomb of the 30th king of Silla,

606
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:45,366
STAFF: King Munmu.

607
00:21:45,499 --> 00:21:46,166
WOOLIN: Oh, really?

608
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:47,799
(Amazed)
NICHOLAS: Is it buried on the island?

609
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:52,864
(The first destination of the school field trip)

610
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:55,712
(It may look like an ordinary rocky island
at first glance)

611
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:59,733
(It's a regal tomb and the world's only
underwater mausoleum!)

612
00:22:00,224 --> 00:22:04,544
(Becoming a dragon of the sea,
just like the will to protect Silla)

613
00:22:05,199 --> 00:22:08,099
(Above the East Sea)

614
00:22:08,099 --> 00:22:13,033
(The Great Rock keeps watch over Gyeongju)

615
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:14,666
STAFF: The 30th king, Munmu,

616
00:22:16,066 --> 00:22:19,499
(After the explanation time)
STAFF: requested to be buried at sea.

617
00:22:19,499 --> 00:22:22,933
STAFF: Let's line up slightly diagonal at 45 degrees.

618
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:25,728
STAFF: We need the Tomb of King Munmu
in the background. Gently hold your knees.

619
00:22:26,464 --> 00:22:28,499
(A signature 90s pose)
STAFF: And smile.

620
00:22:28,499 --> 00:22:29,856
(Commemorating WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL's
school field trip to Gyeongju in September 1996)

621
00:22:29,856 --> 00:22:31,422
TRAINEE: Can't we take pictures like this
at each location?

622
00:22:31,422 --> 00:22:32,992
- TRAINEE: All like this? Good!
- TRAINEE: Like this.

623
00:22:33,399 --> 00:22:34,566
STAFF: We will stay here

624
00:22:34,566 --> 00:22:35,633
STAFF: for five minutes!

625
00:22:35,633 --> 00:22:37,199
STAFF: I'm giving you free time.

626
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,066
(As it's a one-day trip,
the remaining schedule is packed)

627
00:22:40,832 --> 00:22:43,466
(10 minutes. Today's schedule is quite tight)

628
00:22:44,736 --> 00:22:45,568
JUSTIN: Mr. WOOLIN.

629
00:22:47,066 --> 00:22:48,672
TRAINEE: Finding the crabs.

630
00:22:50,566 --> 00:22:52,051
WOOLIN: Owaaah!

631
00:22:52,966 --> 00:22:55,138
TRAINEE: Wow, this looks good, it feels nice.

632
00:22:55,866 --> 00:22:57,133
TRAINEE: WOOLIN, jump!

633
00:22:57,696 --> 00:22:59,136
TRAINEE: WOOLIN.

634
00:22:59,566 --> 00:23:00,866
(Here?)
TRAINEE: Go in.

635
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,699
(Determined to leave one person out)

636
00:23:04,032 --> 00:23:06,733
HYUNJUN: Everyone, everyone. I'll show you 'In Summer'.

637
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:10,053
(Back then, whenever you went to the seaside,
dancing was a must)

638
00:23:10,053 --> 00:23:11,456
(Provided by: Wide Company)

639
00:23:11,766 --> 00:23:15,166
(A rule dance for the seaside)

640
00:23:17,024 --> 00:23:20,599
(DEUX's 'In Summer')

641
00:23:20,768 --> 00:23:22,112
(How students in the '90s spent their free time)
HYUNJUN: Look to the sky.

642
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:23,616
TRAINEE: Sky.

643
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:25,733
(Learn from the dance club friends)
- HYUNJUN: Shoulders. - TRAINEE: Shoulders.

644
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,520
(Choreography for the latest hit song)
- HYUNJUN: Waist. - TRAINEE: Waist.

645
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,446
HYUNJUN: Again.

646
00:23:28,446 --> 00:23:29,376
TRAINEE: Again.

647
00:23:29,376 --> 00:23:31,040
HYUNJUN: Five, six, seven, eight.

648
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:33,760
(Hands facing the opposite direction)
HYUNJUN: The sky is facing us.

649
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,136
JUSTIN: It isn't, though.

650
00:23:35,299 --> 00:23:35,966
(Freeze)

651
00:23:36,733 --> 00:23:37,846
(Friends strangely strict about dancing)
JUSTIN: Why is it wrong?

652
00:23:37,846 --> 00:23:38,966
WOOLIN: What is it?

653
00:23:38,966 --> 00:23:40,544
- TRAINEE: Okay.
- HYUNJUN: Smile, smile.

654
00:23:41,766 --> 00:23:43,299
(Sunny?)

655
00:23:45,472 --> 00:23:47,666
(Dancing with friends at the summer sea)
HYUNJUN: Five, six, seven, eight.

656
00:23:48,256 --> 00:23:51,040
(In the summer)

657
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:54,599
JUSTIN: Why are you so excited?

658
00:23:54,899 --> 00:23:56,699
(Happiness)

659
00:23:57,366 --> 00:24:01,280
(Since I'm with friends,
it will remain in my memory longer)

660
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:04,352
(Our school field trip, just begun)

661
00:24:05,312 --> 00:24:06,208
HYUNJUN: Let's go!

662
00:24:15,488 --> 00:24:16,733
TRAINEE: You hit my head. My head.

663
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:19,533
(After the free time at Tomb of King Munmu)
TRAINEE: My head was hit.

664
00:24:19,744 --> 00:24:21,760
TRAINEE: How long are we going to stay like this?

665
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:23,996
(Still hanging on)
HAMIN: I'm really scared!

666
00:24:23,996 --> 00:24:25,366
TRAINEE: Come down quickly.

667
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:26,400
(Finally, HAMIN feels brave enough to jump)
HAMIN: Here I go.

668
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,232
TRAINEE: Yeah, let's go.

669
00:24:27,232 --> 00:24:27,996
HAMIN: Count for me. Count.

670
00:24:27,996 --> 00:24:28,766
TRAINEE: I'll take a cool picture of you.

671
00:24:28,766 --> 00:24:30,666
ALL: One, two, three.

672
00:24:31,899 --> 00:24:33,499
(Failed)

673
00:24:33,499 --> 00:24:35,233
(Courage -100)
TRAINEE: That's really lame.

674
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:36,960
(Flood of criticism)
JAEWON: What made you so confident to climb up there?

675
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,976
DANIEL: Yeah, you can't even come down.

676
00:24:38,976 --> 00:24:40,480
TRAINEE: You just need to let go of your hand.

677
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,688
HAMIN: I really can't let go.

678
00:24:42,688 --> 00:24:44,928
(Hand stuck with glue)
HAMIN: I really can't let go.

679
00:24:44,928 --> 00:24:46,176
HAMIN: No, no!

680
00:24:46,176 --> 00:24:47,968
HAMIN: I really can't let go. I really can't let go.

681
00:24:48,066 --> 00:24:48,672
(I see)
DANIEL: Got it.

682
00:24:48,672 --> 00:24:50,366
HARUTA: Come quickly.

683
00:24:50,366 --> 00:24:51,466
DANIEL: What am I supposed to do then!

684
00:24:51,499 --> 00:24:52,599
DANIEL: Just stay there and live?

685
00:24:52,599 --> 00:24:53,808
(HAMIN should just live there)
DANIEL: Should you just live here? Just?

686
00:24:53,808 --> 00:24:55,008
TRAINEE: We'll come back after dinner.

687
00:24:55,599 --> 00:24:56,866
HAMIN: I'm going, I'm really going.

688
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:58,880
JAEWON: How many times do you need to say it?

689
00:24:59,136 --> 00:25:00,246
(Saying he's going for the millionth time)
HAMIN: No, I'm really, really going.

690
00:25:00,246 --> 00:25:01,056
DANIEL: Let's go, let's go!

691
00:25:01,056 --> 00:25:02,272
