HARUTA: I've seen this a lot on TV.

1150
00:41:15,279 --> 00:41:16,480
HAMIN: Hey, this is so cute! What is this?

1151
00:41:16,498 --> 00:41:17,216
HARUTA: What is this?

1152
00:41:17,216 --> 00:41:19,552
HAMIN: I want to make something like this! Like these!

1153
00:41:19,552 --> 00:41:22,176
- HARUTA: You can't do it like that.
- HAMIN: No, I'll show you.

1154
00:41:22,816 --> 00:41:28,266
(Ceramics studio run by a master)
STAFF: This studio is actually run by the craftsman.

1155
00:41:28,771 --> 00:41:31,328
(Awarded the title of
Gyeongsangnam Province's Master Craftsman)

1156
00:41:31,666 --> 00:41:33,733
(Suddenly standing)
ALL: Hello!

1157
00:41:33,899 --> 00:41:35,733
(POTTERY TEACHER, Master LEE HANGIL)

1158
00:41:35,733 --> 00:41:39,099
POTTERY TEACHER: Nice to meet you.
This is our pottery workshop.

1159
00:41:39,099 --> 00:41:41,472
POTTERY TEACHER: How to experience pottery?

1160
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:43,266
POTTERY TEACHER: Today, to make the pottery,

1161
00:41:43,266 --> 00:41:45,632
POTTERY TEACHER: just listening to simple instructions
and making it should be helpful.

1162
00:41:45,728 --> 00:41:46,784
DANIEL: Yes.

1163
00:41:46,816 --> 00:41:48,448
(Types of ceramics to experience today)
POTTERY TEACHER: The manufacturing process includes

1164
00:41:48,544 --> 00:41:49,766
POTTERY TEACHER: the potter's wheel and hand shaping.

1165
00:41:49,766 --> 00:41:51,968
(Potter's wheel and hand shaping)
POTTERY TEACHER: Today you will try hand shaping.

1166
00:41:52,128 --> 00:41:57,366
POTTERY TEACHER: The potter's wheel shaping
requires a certain level of skill.

1167
00:41:57,366 --> 00:41:59,392
CHARLIE: Ugh, ouch.

1168
00:41:59,633 --> 00:42:01,366
(Likely to end up like this)

1169
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:05,633
(Offering lots of help)
HAMIN: The teacher is doing everything.

1170
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,008
(Teacher demonstrates first)
POTTERY TEACHER: Now, this...

1171
00:42:07,008 --> 00:42:09,466
POTTERY TEACHER: Potter's wheel shaping
is a "core exercise".

1172
00:42:09,466 --> 00:42:11,872
(Core)
POTTERY TEACHER: How you find balance is important.

1173
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:13,984
POTTERY TEACHER: For example...

1174
00:42:14,528 --> 00:42:16,000
(Shape captured instantly with one touch)

1175
00:42:16,100 --> 00:42:16,966
HARUTA: That's fascinating.

1176
00:42:16,966 --> 00:42:17,984
DANIEL: That's so sexy!

1177
00:42:19,936 --> 00:42:21,866
(The beauty of craftsmanship)

1178
00:42:21,888 --> 00:42:24,192
POTTERY TEACHER: Place it between your hands...

1179
00:42:24,672 --> 00:42:25,600
(The shape changes with every slight movement)

1180
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:27,136
POTTERY TEACHER: and gently spread the clay out.

1181
00:42:29,833 --> 00:42:32,166
(Pottery that looks like a magic trick
unfolding before your eyes)

1182
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:34,816
POTTERY TEACHER: And that's how you create a shape.

1183
00:42:34,912 --> 00:42:36,416
(Quickly completed one bowl)
TRAINEE: That was quick.

1184
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:38,816
TRAINEE: It popped out just like that.

1185
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:42,848
POTTERY TEACHER: This is how you make it. Now sit here.

1186
00:42:42,848 --> 00:42:45,376
(Pottery experience begins)
POTTERY TEACHER: Let's learn how to control the speed.

1187
00:42:45,728 --> 00:42:46,848
HAMIN: Who wants to go first?

1188
00:42:47,133 --> 00:42:49,200
DANIEL: Me, me, me, me, me!

1189
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:51,968
("Wheel throwing" team, JAEWON and DANIEL)
JAEWON: Like this? I'm doing it right now.

1190
00:42:52,566 --> 00:42:55,266
("Hand-building" team, HAMIN and HARUTA and CHARLIE)
HARUTA: I want to make something like this.

1191
00:42:55,466 --> 00:42:58,464
(CHARLIE displays samples following the other members)

1192
00:42:58,464 --> 00:42:59,840
DANIEL: What are you going to make?

1193
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:01,966
(Something huge!)
JAEWON: I want to make something huge.

1194
00:43:01,966 --> 00:43:03,466
(Simple)
DANIEL: You're making something huge?

1195
00:43:03,666 --> 00:43:07,488
(Keeping the clay moist for smoother shaping,
First wet the hands)

1196
00:43:07,712 --> 00:43:08,512
(Touch)

1197
00:43:08,833 --> 00:43:11,066
(A texture they've never felt before)

1198
00:43:11,066 --> 00:43:13,600
POTTERY TEACHER: Use the foot pedal to control
the wheel speed. Don't make it spin too fast.

1199
00:43:13,792 --> 00:43:15,328
DANIEL: It's not working!

1200
00:43:15,367 --> 00:43:16,704
DANIEL: Why is this happening?

1201
00:43:16,864 --> 00:43:18,766
POTTERY TEACHER: Try pressing with your thumb.

1202
00:43:18,933 --> 00:43:20,768
(First step taken with the teacher's help)

1203
00:43:21,019 --> 00:43:21,856
(Whoa)

1204
00:43:22,592 --> 00:43:23,584
(Peek-a-boo)

1205
00:43:24,300 --> 00:43:25,600
(Teacher makes an emergency dispatch)
DANIEL: What do I do?

1206
00:43:27,633 --> 00:43:29,833
(Out of control)

1207
00:43:32,066 --> 00:43:33,312
(Teacher, it's too late to stop)

1208
00:43:33,312 --> 00:43:35,200
POTTERY TEACHER: Slow down, slow down.

1209
00:43:35,296 --> 00:43:37,766
(It hasn't even been a minute,
and they're already getting loud)

1210
00:43:37,933 --> 00:43:39,833
(Making engine sounds with his mouth)

1211
00:43:40,033 --> 00:43:42,733
(Focusing intensely with fingertips)

1212
00:43:42,733 --> 00:43:44,433
DANIEL: Hey, I'm kind of getting it!

1213
00:43:44,533 --> 00:43:45,600
(A surprisingly stable shape)

1214
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:46,432
DANIEL: What are you doing?

1215
00:43:47,700 --> 00:43:48,672
(A technique never seen before?)

1216
00:43:48,672 --> 00:43:50,080
POTTERY TEACHER: Please slow it down.

1217
00:43:50,432 --> 00:43:52,416
(The teacher's hands step in again)
POTTERY TEACHER: Slowly.

1218
00:43:53,538 --> 00:43:54,720
HAMIN: Oh, you're pretty good at this.

1219
00:43:55,072 --> 00:43:56,064
DANIEL: It's easy.

1220
00:43:57,173 --> 00:43:58,688
HAMIN: Oh, JAEWON's got some skill.

1221
00:43:59,280 --> 00:44:00,640
JAEWON: Shall I go for it now?

1222
00:44:01,166 --> 00:44:02,833
(The praise rekindled his racing instincts)

1223
00:44:05,766 --> 00:44:07,424
POTTERY TEACHER: Slow down.

1224
00:44:07,456 --> 00:44:08,896
JAEWON: Can I use all this clay?

1225
00:44:09,943 --> 00:44:10,592
DANIEL: No.

1226
00:44:10,592 --> 00:44:12,096
HAMIN: How big are you planning to make it?

1227
00:44:12,256 --> 00:44:14,166
(Reasonable doubt)
DANIEL: You want to drink milk with that?

1228
00:44:14,300 --> 00:44:16,466
(He can't exactly deny it)

1229
00:44:16,666 --> 00:44:18,656
(After teasing the youngest, they focus again)

1230
00:44:18,752 --> 00:44:19,680
DANIEL: Whoa.

1231
00:44:19,784 --> 00:44:20,544
DANIEL: Huh?

1232
00:44:21,333 --> 00:44:24,266
(The pottery crumpled in an instant)

1233
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:25,984
(He takes a quick look around)

1234
00:44:25,984 --> 00:44:27,456
DANIEL: Ta-da.

1235
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:29,184
(Finished in just two words)
POTTERY TEACHER: That's what makes it cool.

1236
00:44:29,856 --> 00:44:31,433
HAMIN: Looks like a failure to me.

1237
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:32,544
(Here comes the critic)

1238
00:44:32,576 --> 00:44:33,984
HAMIN: Seems like DANIEL doesn't want to admit it.

1239
00:44:34,718 --> 00:44:36,032
- DANIEL: It's artistic, right?
- POTTERY TEACHER: That's right.

1240
00:44:36,900 --> 00:44:38,733
(Like teacher, like student)

1241
00:44:38,912 --> 00:44:39,744
(DANIEL's first piece completed artistically?)

1242
00:44:39,744 --> 00:44:41,024
POTTERY TEACHER: I'll pick it up and set it down.

1243
00:44:43,616 --> 00:44:46,000
POTTERY TEACHER: Slow down.

1244
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:48,928
(Quickly scurries over to JAEWON's wheel)

1245
00:44:49,024 --> 00:44:50,656
JAEWON: Feeling rushed.

1246
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:53,033
DANIEL: I'm doing well, aren't I, teacher?

1247
00:44:53,100 --> 00:44:54,336
POTTERY TEACHER: Oh, yes.

1248
00:44:54,336 --> 00:44:55,424
POTTERY TEACHER: You've got talent.

1249
00:44:55,424 --> 00:44:56,233
DANIEL: Oh, really?

1250
00:44:56,233 --> 00:44:57,900
(Surprised by unexpected praise)
POTTERY TEACHER: You've got talent.

1251
00:44:57,900 --> 00:44:59,200
HAMIN: That's actually pretty good.

1252
00:44:59,419 --> 00:45:00,608
HARUTA: I guess it's my thing.

1253
00:45:01,440 --> 00:45:02,144
(Tch)

1254
00:45:02,566 --> 00:45:03,733
HAMIN: Just because you got some praise.

1255
00:45:03,733 --> 00:45:05,376
HAMIN: You think you're actually good, huh?

1256
00:45:06,208 --> 00:45:07,633
HARUTA: That's a bit harsh.

1257
00:45:07,633 --> 00:45:09,216
(A quick quarrel, quickly resolved)
HAMIN: Sorry.

1258
00:45:09,866 --> 00:45:12,333
(This time, challenging alone
without the teacher's help)

1259
00:45:12,433 --> 00:45:18,866
(Keeping a steady pace with balanced pressure)

1260
00:45:18,976 --> 00:45:19,927
DANIEL: Whoa.

1261
00:45:20,539 --> 00:45:21,536
POTTERY TEACHER: You're making it well.

1262
00:45:22,065 --> 00:45:23,104
DANIEL: It's done.

1263
00:45:23,456 --> 00:45:26,688
DANIEL: Can I add a little artistic touch here?

1264
00:45:26,800 --> 00:45:30,766
(Gently placing two fingers, engraving artistry)

1265
00:45:30,766 --> 00:45:32,832
POTTERY TEACHER: You've got a much

1266
00:45:32,832 --> 00:45:34,400
POTTERY TEACHER: better feel for it.

1267
00:45:34,694 --> 00:45:35,872
- DANIEL: Better than him, right?
- POTTERY TEACHER: Yes.

1268
00:45:36,512 --> 00:45:37,500
(0 wins and 1 loss)

1269
00:45:37,632 --> 00:45:40,384
DANIEL: Would you consider
taking me as your apprentice?

1270
00:45:43,264 --> 00:45:44,700
HAMIN: It's not that much.

1271
00:45:44,864 --> 00:45:46,733
(Failed career exploration)

1272
00:45:46,933 --> 00:45:47,633
POTTERY TEACHER: Oh.

1273
00:45:47,633 --> 00:45:49,900
POTTERY TEACHER: He's really making a jar?

1274
00:45:49,900 --> 00:45:50,666
POTTERY TEACHER: Good!

1275
00:45:50,666 --> 00:45:51,966
HARUTA: You're doing well.

1276
00:45:52,512 --> 00:45:53,696
(Getting scolded for speed, finally received praise)
DANIEL: Finally pulled one off.

1277
00:45:53,728 --> 00:45:54,524
JAEWON: I made it.

1278
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:57,800
(The sudden praise)

1279
00:45:57,800 --> 00:45:59,744
(Gets them excited again)

1280
00:45:59,882 --> 00:46:00,704
JAEWON: Oh?

1281
00:46:00,704 --> 00:46:02,752
(Leaning Tower of Pisa by JAEWON)

1282
00:46:02,912 --> 00:46:03,776
DANIEL: Hey, that's even better.

1283
00:46:03,904 --> 00:46:05,696
(Received praise from free-spirited artist DANIEL)
DANIEL: Just finish it like this.

1284
00:46:05,952 --> 00:46:07,066
DANIEL: Looks like a duck.

1285
00:46:07,066 --> 00:46:08,160
(Duck-shaped pottery is born)

1286
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:08,960
JAEWON: Really?

1287
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:11,456
JAEWON: Seems opposite.

1288
00:46:13,833 --> 00:46:15,552
(Engraving names on hand-made pottery)

1289
00:46:15,616 --> 00:46:17,184
HARUTA: How about 'WONHA~JANNI'?

1290
00:46:21,833 --> 00:46:24,733
(Also left the name of Class '10)

1291
00:46:24,864 --> 00:46:27,168
DANIEL: Our dorm is going to fill up with these.

1292
00:46:27,418 --> 00:46:29,408
(One month later)

1293
00:46:29,632 --> 00:46:30,240
TRAINEE: Hello.

1294
00:46:30,240 --> 00:46:32,000
(Various hand-made pottery arrived with a bluish glow)
TRAINEE: Oh, pottery.

1295
00:46:32,064 --> 00:46:32,864
TRAINEE: It's mine.

1296
00:46:32,896 --> 00:46:34,688
TRAINEE: Mine's the best made.

1297
00:46:34,900 --> 00:46:35,776
HAMIN: Mine looks cool.

1298
00:46:35,904 --> 00:46:37,000
(HAMIN's thing)
DANIEL: This is really the worst.

1299
00:46:38,218 --> 00:46:39,328
TRAINEE: What does it say?

1300
00:46:39,328 --> 00:46:40,160
HAMIN: WONHA~JANNI.

1301
00:46:40,733 --> 00:46:43,133
HAMIN: Honestly, this is the most practical one here.

1302
00:46:43,133 --> 00:46:45,600
(Everyone bragging about their work)
TRAINEE: Isn't it this one? Honestly.

1303
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:46,816
DANIEL: Artistry.

1304
00:46:46,848 --> 00:46:47,712
(An artistic piece completed in two words, 'Ta-da')

1305
00:46:47,731 --> 00:46:49,600
HAMIN: This happened by accident
while you were making it...

1306
00:46:49,766 --> 00:46:52,736
(Whether it was a mistake or intentional, only he knows)
DANIEL: No, I meant to do that.

1307
00:46:52,916 --> 00:46:53,568
HAMIN: What would you even use this for...

1308
00:46:53,568 --> 00:46:54,880
DANIEL: Honestly, it's more of a decoration.

1309
00:46:55,348 --> 00:46:57,120
(Well)

1310
00:46:57,408 --> 00:46:58,560
HAMIN: So it's not practical.

1311
00:46:58,900 --> 00:47:00,576
(Laugh)
DANIEL: Something like a key, or a lock...

1312
00:47:01,472 --> 00:47:03,776
DANIEL: But once it's all made...

1313
00:47:03,936 --> 00:47:04,766
DANIEL: it looks different!

1314
00:47:04,766 --> 00:47:06,848
JAEWON: I didn't know the color
would turn out so pretty.

1315
00:47:07,358 --> 00:47:08,608
HARUTA: I should give this to my parents.

1316
00:47:08,608 --> 00:47:10,100
(I should give this to my parents!)

1317
00:47:10,100 --> 00:47:11,712
(Ceramics experience class ends)
ALL: Thank you.

1318
00:47:11,846 --> 00:47:12,928
TRAINEE: Thank you for your hard work.

1319
00:47:12,928 --> 00:47:13,984
TRAINEE: It was fun.

1320
00:47:13,984 --> 00:47:14,976
TRAINEE: I've always wanted to try this.

1321
00:47:16,366 --> 00:47:19,666
(Meanwhile, Class '90 is moving again)
STAFF: We're moving to Cheonmachong Tomb now.

1322
00:47:19,966 --> 00:47:22,666
(Next destination is Gyeongju's famous historical site
where Cheonmachong Tomb is located)

1323
00:47:22,944 --> 00:47:24,320
(Third destination of the school field trip)

1324
00:47:24,433 --> 00:47:26,166
(Daereungwon Ancient Tomb Complex)

1325
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:29,766
(Meaning a place with large tombs)

1326
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:32,066
(Including Hwangnamdaechong Tomb)

1327
00:47:32,066 --> 00:47:34,233
(And Cheonmachong Tomb)

1328
00:47:35,266 --> 00:47:38,366
(There are 23 ancient tombs
in Daereungwon Ancient Tomb Complex)

1329
00:47:38,366 --> 00:47:45,933
(Cheonmachong Tomb, which allows
interior viewing, is a 90s school field trip staple)

1330
00:47:46,528 --> 00:47:48,032
(Entering Daereungwon Ancient Tomb Complex)
TRAINEE: Hello.

1331
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:49,440
TRAINEE: It's so pretty.

1332
00:47:51,264 --> 00:47:52,384
NICHOLAS: Is that a tomb?

1333
00:47:52,992 --> 00:47:55,040
NICHOLAS: That's not a tomb, right?

1334
00:47:55,072 --> 00:47:55,968
WOOLIN: Something that big?

1335
00:47:56,224 --> 00:47:57,376
(Incredible tomb size)
NICHOLAS: That can't be it, right?

1336
00:47:57,376 --> 00:47:58,464
HYUNJUN: I think it is.

1337
00:47:58,464 --> 00:47:59,168
WOOLIN: That big?

1338
00:47:59,168 --> 00:48:00,096
NICHOLAS: That big?

1339
00:48:00,533 --> 00:48:03,232
NICHOLAS: Teacher, is that really a tomb?

1340
00:48:03,552 --> 00:48:05,216
(Yes, it really is a tomb)

1341
00:48:05,235 --> 00:48:06,560
TRAINEE: It's really big.

1342
00:48:07,823 --> 00:48:08,864
(Cheonmachong Tomb)
TRAINEE: Can we go inside?

1343
00:48:09,157 --> 00:48:10,080
TRAINEE: Are we just going in?

1344
00:48:11,333 --> 00:48:12,288
(Time to enter the huge tomb)

1345
00:48:12,355 --> 00:48:13,312
TRAINEE: Let's go.

1346
00:48:14,333 --> 00:48:16,466
(Walking into the tomb)

1347
00:48:16,466 --> 00:48:17,700
JUSTIN: Wow, what's this?

1348
00:48:17,837 --> 00:48:18,592
TRAINEE: Wow!

1349
00:48:18,646 --> 00:48:19,552
TRAINEE: Wow!

1350
00:48:20,333 --> 00:48:21,152
JUSTIN: It's preserved just like it was.

1351
00:48:21,171 --> 00:48:21,984
TRAINEE: Wow, it's scary.

1352
00:48:22,766 --> 00:48:25,066
(The interior of the tomb is replicated
just as it was excavated)

1353
00:48:25,333 --> 00:48:27,166
KASSHO: Wow, it's fascinating, really.

1354
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:30,433
(Including the internationally famous
Cheonmachong Tomb golden crown)

1355
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:34,560
(Neatly arranged,
splendid artifacts from the Silla era)

1356
00:48:34,976 --> 00:48:37,216
TRAINEE: Even in BLACKPINK JENNIE's music video,

1357
00:48:37,376 --> 00:48:37,792
TRAINEE: this...

1358
00:48:37,792 --> 00:48:40,480
(The gold crown ornament that inspired JENNIE's outfit)
TRAINEE: She wore it like this.

1359
00:48:41,472 --> 00:48:45,366
HYUNJUN: I hope we can wear
something like that on stage someday.

1360
00:48:45,733 --> 00:48:49,100
STAFF: You'll have 10 minutes to look around.

1361
00:48:49,100 --> 00:48:49,792
TRAINEE: Let's go, let's go.

1362
00:48:49,792 --> 00:48:51,296
TRAINEE: I have to take a lot of pictures.

1363
00:48:52,266 --> 00:48:55,000
(The aspiring rich man is captivated
by the luxurious artifacts)

1364
00:48:57,656 --> 00:48:59,104
JUSTIN: This is amazing.

1365
00:48:59,819 --> 00:49:01,248
TRAINEE: This is the one from earlier...

1366
00:49:01,376 --> 00:49:03,648
TRAINEE: This is the picture that was at the entrance.

1367
00:49:03,664 --> 00:49:05,184
(Symbol of Cheonmachong Tomb, Painting of a Heavenly Horse)
TRAINEE: Painting of a Heavenly Horse.

1368
00:49:06,224 --> 00:49:08,640
TRAINEE: I rode a horse with SIWON in a game once.

1369
00:49:09,533 --> 00:49:12,533
(Thinking of one person when seeing the horse)

1370
00:49:12,819 --> 00:49:13,952
NICHOLAS: Is it real gold?

1371
00:49:14,528 --> 00:49:15,776
NICHOLAS: Real gold?

1372
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,466
(The aspiring rich man reacts only to gold)
NICHOLAS: It must have been gold, right?

1373
