01:04:16,416 --> 01:04:17,088
TRAINEE: It's almost...

1844
01:04:17,088 --> 01:04:17,766
TRAINEE: It's almost like a mirror.

1845
01:04:17,766 --> 01:04:18,688
(Wolji Pond reflects the palace like a mirror)

1846
01:04:18,688 --> 01:04:20,096
TRAINEE: Wow, it's beautiful.

1847
01:04:20,320 --> 01:04:21,728
TRAINEE: Wow, it's so beautiful.

1848
01:04:22,533 --> 01:04:24,100
HYUNJUN: Hey, look at those clouds!

1849
01:04:24,700 --> 01:04:25,766
KASSHO: Wow, it's beautiful.

1850
01:04:26,800 --> 01:04:29,900
(The landscape is made more picturesque
by the moon and clouds)

1851
01:04:30,700 --> 01:04:33,700
(A mesmerizing view that captures the soul)

1852
01:04:34,233 --> 01:04:35,666
JUSTIN: Let's go to the next place.

1853
01:04:36,366 --> 01:04:37,200
KASSHO: Let's go.

1854
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:38,700
WOOLIN: We've got to go all the way to the end!

1855
01:04:38,700 --> 01:04:41,000
WOOLIN: We came all this way, we might never come back!

1856
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:42,266
JUSTIN: We might never come back!

1857
01:04:42,300 --> 01:04:43,712
JUSTIN: We'll definitely come back!

1858
01:04:44,032 --> 01:04:44,288
NICHOLAS: Why?

1859
01:04:44,576 --> 01:04:45,700
WOOLIN: Why are you so sure we'll come back?

1860
01:04:45,700 --> 01:04:47,133
JUSTIN: I just want to come back.

1861
01:04:47,133 --> 01:04:48,533
WOOLIN: Oh, just because you want to?

1862
01:04:48,533 --> 01:04:50,433
NICHOLAS: I think I'd come back just because I want to.

1863
01:04:50,433 --> 01:04:51,840
JUSTIN: Next time too, with HYUNJUN and A.U.I.

1864
01:04:54,112 --> 01:04:55,904
- TRAINEE: It's so pretty.
- TRAINEE: Gyeongju style.

1865
01:04:55,904 --> 01:04:57,833
(Wanting to return to Gyeongju even before leaving)

1866
01:04:58,166 --> 01:04:59,133
WOOLIN: This is so Gyeongju.

1867
01:04:59,133 --> 01:05:00,700
KASSHO: Really beautiful.

1868
01:05:03,066 --> 01:05:04,672
JUSTIN: The lights are so beautiful.

1869
01:05:04,928 --> 01:05:05,536
TRAINEE: I know.

1870
01:05:05,536 --> 01:05:07,072
JUSTIN: The atmosphere... that orange glow.

1871
01:05:07,072 --> 01:05:08,100
(Orange lights coloring
the night of the school field trip)

1872
01:05:08,384 --> 01:05:09,600
KASSHO: I want to keep it like this.

1873
01:05:10,304 --> 01:05:11,520
- JUSTIN: He wants it all.
- KASSHO: To my house...

1874
01:05:11,520 --> 01:05:12,666
(A future rich man's dream garden)

1875
01:05:13,760 --> 01:05:14,656
NICHOLAS: Wow.

1876
01:05:15,733 --> 01:05:18,366
NICHOLAS: It looks beautiful
from every different angle.

1877
01:05:18,366 --> 01:05:19,166
HYUNJUN: Exactly.

1878
01:05:19,166 --> 01:05:19,904
NICHOLAS: It's the best.

1879
01:05:19,904 --> 01:05:20,600
HYUNJUN: It's the best.

1880
01:05:20,600 --> 01:05:22,304
(Wolji pond looks newly beautiful from new angles)

1881
01:05:22,304 --> 01:05:22,966
HYUNJUN: By the way...

1882
01:05:22,966 --> 01:05:26,800
HYUNJUN: Those tiled roofs are perfectly symmetrical.

1883
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:27,840
HYUNJUN: I heard that somewhere.

1884
01:05:28,256 --> 01:05:29,664
(Trivia King OH HYUNJUN(?))
HYUNJUN: It's perfectly symmetrical.

1885
01:05:30,166 --> 01:05:32,166
HYUNJUN: That's why it feels calming
every time I look at it.

1886
01:05:33,366 --> 01:05:34,720
TRAINEE: I wish my face was like that too.

1887
01:05:35,968 --> 01:05:36,896
(Don't worry)
HYUNJUN: It's so pretty.

1888
01:05:38,272 --> 01:05:39,392
WOOLIN: Is this a tomb too?

1889
01:05:40,032 --> 01:05:40,736
JUSTIN: Where?

1890
01:05:40,736 --> 01:05:41,536
WOOLIN: Here, here.

1891
01:05:41,766 --> 01:05:42,240
(A tomb at Donggung Palace and Wolji Pond?)

1892
01:05:42,240 --> 01:05:43,104
WOOLIN: Sounds possible, right?

1893
01:05:43,648 --> 01:05:44,896
JUSTIN: Is this also a tomb?

1894
01:05:46,272 --> 01:05:47,300
JUSTIN: This isn't a tomb, right?

1895
01:05:47,300 --> 01:05:47,840
(It's just a hill)
TRAINEE: Oh, it isn't?

1896
01:05:47,840 --> 01:05:48,512
STAFF: It's just a hill.

1897
01:05:49,792 --> 01:05:51,500
WOOLIN: You never know though.

1898
01:05:51,566 --> 01:05:53,500
WOOLIN: What if you dig and there's something inside?

1899
01:05:54,400 --> 01:05:55,104
WOOLIN: After all, it's Gyeongju.

1900
01:05:55,104 --> 01:05:55,968
JUSTIN: It's Gyeongju.

1901
01:05:56,833 --> 01:05:59,232
(It's fortunate if you learned anything...)
WOOLIN: The moon is pretty now.

1902
01:05:59,904 --> 01:06:02,400
(The deepening night of Gyeongju as they walk)
TRAINEE: It's hidden by clouds.

1903
01:06:02,688 --> 01:06:03,936
HYUNJUN: Hey, how much allowance do we have left?

1904
01:06:04,256 --> 01:06:05,856
(The reason for the sudden financial check?)
JUSTIN: I spent all my allowance earlier.

1905
01:06:05,856 --> 01:06:06,432
KASSHO: Why?

1906
01:06:06,880 --> 01:06:08,352
JUSTIN: I used it all to buy ten-won bread.

1907
01:06:09,200 --> 01:06:11,966
(The last shopping opportunity not to be missed)

1908
01:06:12,736 --> 01:06:14,016
NICHOLAS: Oh, this...

1909
01:06:15,166 --> 01:06:16,416
(Found accessory used on the crown)
NICHOLAS: Jade?

1910
01:06:16,416 --> 01:06:17,824
(shaped like a comma-shaped jewel)
TRAINEE: Oh, it's really...

1911
01:06:17,824 --> 01:06:18,624
TRAINEE: It's pretty.

1912
01:06:19,200 --> 01:06:20,433
KASSHO: I have no money!

1913
01:06:20,833 --> 01:06:21,952
(A flute shaped like a magic flute)
KASSHO: Recorder. Ocarina.

1914
01:06:21,952 --> 01:06:22,688
KASSHO: Oh.

1915
01:06:23,000 --> 01:06:24,266
KASSHO: It's pretty though?

1916
01:06:24,700 --> 01:06:26,166
KASSHO: But can you afford this? Look at it.

1917
01:06:26,533 --> 01:06:28,033
(Everywhere, the price is always the issue)

1918
01:06:28,400 --> 01:06:30,100
KASSHO: I don't have money.

1919
01:06:30,166 --> 01:06:32,500
TEACHER: A souvenir to remember today.

1920
01:06:32,500 --> 01:06:34,166
TEACHER: Each person can choose just one.

1921
01:06:34,166 --> 01:06:34,560
WOOLIN: Oh.

1922
01:06:35,168 --> 01:06:35,600
WOOLIN: Thank you.

1923
01:06:35,600 --> 01:06:36,192
HYUNJUN: You're buying it for us?

1924
01:06:36,192 --> 01:06:37,216
(How could anyone ignore such hopeful faces?)

1925
01:06:37,344 --> 01:06:38,464
TRAINEE: Wow, really?

1926
01:06:38,900 --> 01:06:40,566
HYUNJUN: I will likely play it a lot in the future.

1927
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:42,466
(Choosing the magic flute said to bring peace)
HYUNJUN: Let's play it when times are tough in the practice room.

1928
01:06:42,466 --> 01:06:43,633
JUSTIN: Ah, I'm torn.

1929
01:06:43,633 --> 01:06:45,700
JUSTIN: Should I get the big one or the small one?

1930
01:06:45,700 --> 01:06:47,392
JUSTIN: Which do you think is better? The big one?

1931
01:06:47,392 --> 01:06:49,248
(Carefully choosing just one souvenir)

1932
01:06:50,336 --> 01:06:51,264
WOOLIN: Ta-da.

1933
01:06:53,888 --> 01:06:57,266
(The school field trip souvenirs purchased on this day)

1934
01:06:58,112 --> 01:06:59,264
(One month later, in the practice room)

1935
01:06:59,264 --> 01:07:00,032
JUSTIN: Take out the earring?

1936
01:07:00,500 --> 01:07:01,152
(JUSTIN's cherished item became these earrings)

1937
01:07:01,152 --> 01:07:01,952
JUSTIN: Ah, always...

1938
01:07:03,136 --> 01:07:04,000
JUSTIN: I wear it all the time.

1939
01:07:04,832 --> 01:07:05,376
TRAINEE: Let's go.

1940
01:07:05,376 --> 01:07:09,333
(The memories of Gyeongju
shining from JUSTIN's earrings)

1941
01:07:09,333 --> 01:07:10,866
(On the day of the WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL festival)

1942
01:07:10,866 --> 01:07:12,133
(Even on the festival stage, JUSTIN wears the earrings)

1943
01:07:12,500 --> 01:07:14,900
(NICHOLAS wears the necklace)

1944
01:07:15,200 --> 01:07:16,064
(For reference, NICHOLAS' top treasure is...)

1945
01:07:16,064 --> 01:07:17,376
NICHOLAS: This necklace.

1946
01:07:18,100 --> 01:07:20,600
NICHOLAS: My parents bought it for me.

1947
01:07:20,640 --> 01:07:25,000
(Replacing the necklace he never took off)
NICHOLAS: I've barely switched it since getting it.

1948
01:07:25,888 --> 01:07:30,240
(A glowing green pendant on NICHOLAS's neck)

1949
01:07:31,872 --> 01:07:32,736
(Precious memories from the school field trip)

1950
01:07:32,736 --> 01:07:33,408
JUSTIN: Be careful.

1951
01:07:36,333 --> 01:07:38,566
NICHOLAS: Did the other classes
have such a romantic trip too?

1952
01:07:38,566 --> 01:07:40,320
TRAINEE: No way, this is pure '90s vibe.

1953
01:07:40,416 --> 01:07:42,784
TRAINEE: So, I think only the 90s.

1954
01:07:42,944 --> 01:07:43,904
TRAINEE: '90s romance.

1955
01:07:44,966 --> 01:07:48,400
(A time they've never personally experienced,)

1956
01:07:49,266 --> 01:07:53,033
(they learned the romance of the '90s on this trip)

1957
01:07:53,856 --> 01:07:55,833
(Memories just for the five of us)

1958
01:07:56,300 --> 01:07:57,664
(Class '00 returning from the experiential learning)
TRAINEE: Why does school feel like home now?

1959
01:07:57,856 --> 01:07:58,528
TRAINEE: That's what I'm saying.

1960
01:07:59,533 --> 01:08:03,133
(Back here at the school that feels like home)

1961
01:08:03,633 --> 01:08:07,700
(The boys naturally gather in the lounge)

1962
01:08:08,352 --> 01:08:10,560
TATA: Oh, HANBI, still so full.

1963
01:08:10,560 --> 01:08:12,566
HANBI: I'm really so full too.

1964
01:08:12,566 --> 01:08:14,833
HANBI: I'm so full it's driving me crazy.

1965
01:08:14,833 --> 01:08:16,384
HANBI: Oh, I can't move.

1966
01:08:17,504 --> 01:08:19,712
HANBI: I still have to write my journal though.

1967
01:08:20,600 --> 01:08:22,533
(Sound echoing in the hallway at that time)

1968
01:08:22,566 --> 01:08:25,233
(Class '90 appears, glowing with excitement)

1969
01:08:28,433 --> 01:08:30,233
(Checking the lounge as soon as they arrive)

1970
01:08:30,432 --> 01:08:31,712
HYUNJUN: We missed you guys.

1971
01:08:32,320 --> 01:08:33,536
HANBI: Oh, you're here.

1972
01:08:34,466 --> 01:08:36,366
HYUNJUN: We brought ten-won bread and barley bread.

1973
01:08:36,480 --> 01:08:38,144
(Bringing food gifts they bought)
HANBI: Ah, you went to Gyeongju, right?

1974
01:08:38,432 --> 01:08:39,424
HYUNJUN: These are famous there.

1975
01:08:39,866 --> 01:08:40,800
SADAHARU: I want to eat!

1976
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:41,632
HYUNJUN: Go ahead.

1977
01:08:42,100 --> 01:08:44,166
HANBI: How did you manage a one-day-trip to Gyeongju?

1978
01:08:44,166 --> 01:08:46,528
HYUNJUN: It was a one-day school trip concept.

1979
01:08:46,528 --> 01:08:47,424
HANBI: Wow, that's amazing.

1980
01:08:47,616 --> 01:08:49,333
HANBI: We were just drawing!

1981
01:08:49,333 --> 01:08:50,800
NICHOLAS: Oh, right, I heard about it.

1982
01:08:50,800 --> 01:08:52,384
(Taking out the souvenirs they bought)
TRAINEE: Ah.

1983
01:08:52,832 --> 01:08:53,536
(Suddenly)
TRAINEE: Wow.

1984
01:08:53,833 --> 01:08:54,752
(Trying to tempt HANBI)
TRAINEE: Maybe later...

1985
01:08:54,912 --> 01:08:56,096
TRAINEE: Great.

1986
01:08:56,352 --> 01:08:58,240
(The eldest falls for it immediately)
HANBI: Oh, me too.

1987
01:08:59,166 --> 01:09:00,833
HANBI: Oh wow, it's actually metal!

1988
01:09:00,833 --> 01:09:02,336
WOOLIN: Yeah, it's the real deal.

1989
01:09:02,528 --> 01:09:03,200
(Fiddling)

1990
01:09:03,200 --> 01:09:03,700
NICHOLAS: HYUNJUN's is the best.

1991
01:09:03,700 --> 01:09:05,266
HYUNJUN: You can do this when practice gets tough!

1992
01:09:05,766 --> 01:09:07,133
(Another item appears)

1993
01:09:07,133 --> 01:09:08,633
HANBI: Hey, let's bring this to our practice room!

1994
01:09:08,832 --> 01:09:09,696
HANBI: This and this.

1995
01:09:10,500 --> 01:09:12,700
(Soon, a solemn sound echoes through the school)

1996
01:09:12,700 --> 01:09:13,280
HYUNJUN: Sounds good?

1997
01:09:13,280 --> 01:09:13,984
HANBI: Sounds good?

1998
01:09:13,984 --> 01:09:15,700
HANBI: And then we all sit down together...

1999
01:09:15,700 --> 01:09:17,700
HANBI: Alright, everyone, before we start practice,

2000
01:09:17,700 --> 01:09:19,136
HANBI: let's calm our breathing first.

2001
01:09:19,136 --> 01:09:20,032
HANBI: Turn off the lights.

2002
01:09:20,266 --> 01:09:21,216
(He does everything seriously)
TRAINEE: Alright, definitely...

2003
01:09:21,216 --> 01:09:21,952
HANBI: Turn it off.

2004
01:09:22,466 --> 01:09:24,700
HANBI: We will have some time to meditate.

2005
01:09:24,700 --> 01:09:27,166
HANBI: Everyone, silence.

2006
01:09:29,166 --> 01:09:33,733
(While they sink into meditation...)

2007
01:09:33,733 --> 01:09:35,433
(Class '10 arrives at the school)

2008
01:09:35,433 --> 01:09:36,608
HARUTA: It was fun.

2009
01:09:36,992 --> 01:09:38,720
CHARLIE: It was really fun.

2010
01:09:40,352 --> 01:09:41,536
JAEWON: What, where is everyone?

2011
01:09:41,536 --> 01:09:42,304
DANIEL: No one here?

2012
01:09:42,496 --> 01:09:43,136
JAEWON: There's nobody here.

2013
01:09:43,136 --> 01:09:44,433
DANIEL: They're probably in the lounge.

2014
01:09:44,433 --> 01:09:44,960
(Room 202)

2015
01:09:45,024 --> 01:09:45,472
DANIEL: Yo.

2016
01:09:46,464 --> 01:09:47,392
TATA: Hello.

2017
01:09:48,766 --> 01:09:52,466
NICHOLAS: There's ten-won bread
and Gyeongju bread there, so try some.

2018
01:09:52,466 --> 01:09:53,984
DANIEL: Oh right, you went to Gyeongju.

2019
01:09:53,984 --> 01:09:54,976
DANIEL: Was it fun?

2020
01:09:54,976 --> 01:09:56,480
NICHOLAS: It was totally like... this.

2021
01:09:56,672 --> 01:09:58,400
NICHOLAS: Kind of this vibe.

2022
01:09:58,976 --> 01:10:02,300
(NICHOLAS expressing with his whole body)
NICHOLAS: It felt kind of like visiting a temple...

2023
01:10:03,392 --> 01:10:04,128
NICHOLAS: It was so fun.

2024
01:10:04,224 --> 01:10:05,824
DANIEL: Ours was more like "whoa!"

2025
01:10:05,933 --> 01:10:08,133
NICHOLAS: Oh, you guys?
I thought you guys might feel that way.

2026
01:10:08,768 --> 01:10:10,112
(After finishing untold stories)
- TRAINEE: Did everyone go to shower? - TRAINEE: Yeah.

2027
01:10:10,848 --> 01:10:11,360
TRAINEE: Really?

2028
01:10:12,433 --> 01:10:14,366
SONGHA: Let's go practice the 'Into The New World'
choreography now.

2029
01:10:14,592 --> 01:10:15,300
HANBI: Let's go.

2030
01:10:15,488 --> 01:10:16,640
(Everyone moving to the auditorium for festival practice)
HANBI: Let's wrap it up.

2031
01:10:17,248 --> 01:10:18,496
HANBI: To wrap things up.

2032
01:10:19,133 --> 01:10:22,300
(D-25 until the festival)

2033
01:10:22,368 --> 01:10:23,072
TRAINEE: I'll play it.

2034
01:10:23,584 --> 01:10:24,128
TRAINEE: Alright.

2035
01:10:24,800 --> 01:10:26,300
HANBI: Let's warm up, everyone.

2036
01:10:26,833 --> 01:10:28,666
(Now it's the familiar routine music)
- TRAINEE: Okay. - TRAINEE: Let's go.

2037
01:10:28,666 --> 01:10:30,720
SONGHA: Perfectly. Hey, Class '10, move up front.

2038
01:10:30,912 --> 01:10:33,472
SONGHA: Class '10, move up front.

2039
01:10:33,472 --> 01:10:34,016
(They quickly shuffle forward)

2040
01:10:34,656 --> 01:10:35,264
TRAINEE: What?

2041
01:10:35,264 --> 01:10:37,700
(First-place class, they start warming up
following the 'WONHA~JANNI' class)

2042
01:10:38,933 --> 01:10:40,400
KASSHO: Where's Class '90?

2043
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:41,824
TRAINEE: Start.

2044
01:10:41,824 --> 01:10:42,766
(Class '90 joins in quickly)

2045
01:10:43,104 --> 01:10:43,840
(Glance)

2046
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:44,512
KASSHO: TATA.

2047
01:10:44,900 --> 01:10:46,560
(Using hand signals to find TATA's spot)
TRAINEE: Okay.

2048
01:10:46,560 --> 01:10:48,256
TRAINEE: Definitely a warm-up.

2049
01:10:48,533 --> 01:10:51,366
(While not missing any moves, finding Class '00)

2050
01:10:51,456 --> 01:10:52,200
(JUSTIN, HANBI)

2051
01:10:52,200 --> 01:10:55,500
(Exchange students)

2052
01:10:56,400 --> 01:10:58,080
DANIEL: If you do this diligently,
it really relaxes you!

2053
01:10:58,304 --> 01:10:59,232
HAMIN: Right, if you work hard, it really eases.

2054
01:11:00,224 --> 01:11:00,960
HAMIN: Ah.

2055
01:11:03,168 --> 01:11:03,936
HAMIN: We need to move.

2056
01:11:05,433 --> 01:11:07,233
(Idol routine, featuring wooden fish)

2057
01:11:07,233 --> 01:11:07,900
HAMIN: Chest.

2058
01:11:07,900 --> 01:11:08,736
(Chest exercise that requires holding hands)

2059
01:11:08,736 --> 01:11:09,120
TRAINEE: TATA.

2060
01:11:09,504 --> 01:11:11,296
(Joining in by walking backward)

2061
01:11:11,584 --> 01:11:13,120
(Start)

2062
01:11:13,440 --> 01:11:14,800
(End)
TRAINEE: It's really long.

2063
01:11:14,800 --> 01:11:15,520
TRAINEE: It's too long.

2064
01:11:15,520 --> 01:11:16,992
(It takes forever to get from end to end)
TRAINEE: We're the shortest.

2065
01:11:16,992 --> 01:11:18,368
SONGHA: We need to be fast.

2066
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:20,966
(The peaceful two)

2067
01:11:21,400 --> 01:11:23,328
(Choreography for 'Into The New World')
TRAINEE: Hey, this part's coming soon.

2068
01:11:23,328 --> 01:11:24,096
TRAINEE: Prepare a lot.

2069
01:11:25,700 --> 01:11:28,066
(Everyone working hard, groaning)

2070
01:11:29,280 --> 01:11:30,048
SONGHA: Oh, dear.

2071
01:11:30,208 --> 01:11:31,136
DANIEL: Oh my, oh my.

2072
01:11:32,224 --> 01:11:32,896
TRAINEE: Free, free.

2073
01:11:32,992 --> 01:11:33,728
(Not this one)
WOOLIN: Oh right, this one.

2074
01:11:34,304 --> 01:11:35,040
TRAINEE: Oh right, this one.

2075
01:11:35,200 --> 01:11:36,833
TRAINEES: Cutely.

2076
01:11:37,920 --> 01:11:39,392
KASSHO: Make it adorable.

2077
01:11:39,392 --> 01:11:41,056
SONGHA: Oh, SA... SADAHARU is cute.

2078
01:11:41,056 --> 01:11:43,100
- TRAINEE: Cutely.
- TRAINEE: SADAHARU is cute.

2079
01:11:43,100 --> 01:11:44,192
(SADAHARU's adorableness)
TRAINEE: SADAHARU is cute.

2080
01:11:44,192 --> 01:11:45,184
TRAINEE: Oh, make it adorable.

2081
01:11:45,792 --> 01:11:46,880
TRAINEE: Ballerina.

2082
01:11:46,880 --> 01:11:48,333
(Next, ballet moves)

2083
01:11:48,333 --> 01:11:49,120
NICHOLAS: Show us, WOOLIN.

2084
01:11:49,120 --> 01:11:49,984
- JAEWON: Show us, WOOLIN.
- TRAINEE: Extend it.

2085
01:11:50,208 --> 01:11:51,166
TRAINEE: Show us, WOOLIN.

2086
01:11:51,166 --> 01:11:52,256
TRAINEE: WOOLIN.

2087
01:11:52,256 --> 01:11:53,766
(Class '90's "butterfly" flies forward)
TRAINEE: Why...

2088
01:11:55,533 --> 01:11:57,184
(Wooden fish floats around the butterfly)
TRAINEE: Wow.

2089
01:11:57,184 --> 01:11:57,984
TRAINEE: Flying.

2090
01:11:57,984 --> 01:11:59,066
TRAINEE: Let's go! Let's go!

2091
01:11:59,808 --> 01:12:00,928
TRAINEE: Ahaha.

2092
01:12:01,664 --> 01:12:02,080
(Bam!)

2093
01:12:03,300 --> 01:12:04,832
(Focusing more on hitting
the wooden fish than the moves)

2094
01:12:04,896 --> 01:12:05,760
TRAINEE: Need to lift your foot.

2095
01:12:05,760 --> 01:12:06,368
CHARLIE: Lift your leg.

2096
01:12:06,368 --> 01:12:07,266
TRAINEE: My shoes keep slipping.

2097
01:12:07,266 --> 01:12:08,768
- TRAINEE: Lift your leg.
- TRAINEE: I picked the wrong shoes.

2098
01:12:08,768 --> 01:12:10,784
(Can't lift the legs but at least using the upper body)

2099
01:12:10,784 --> 01:12:11,968
JAEWON: Energetically!

2100
01:12:15,936 --> 01:12:16,544
CHARLIE: What is this?

2101
01:12:16,864 --> 01:12:18,976
(Forming the duo of wooden percussion)

2102
01:12:22,100 --> 01:12:24,333
(Catching their breath with inner peace)

2103
01:12:25,696 --> 01:12:26,464
TRAINEE: This is hard.

2104
01:12:30,592 --> 01:12:31,712
(Ugh)

2105
01:12:32,960 --> 01:12:33,664
JAEWON: Do it together.

2106
01:12:36,000 --> 01:12:37,800
(Warm-ups finished!)

2107
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:39,533
HANBI: How is it? So, did your bodies loosen up?

2108
01:12:39,533 --> 01:12:40,333
HYUNJUN: Yes, I'm loosened up.

2109
01:12:40,500 --> 01:12:42,200
DANIEL: I'm loosened up, ah, it's so refreshing.

2110
01:12:42,866 --> 01:12:45,300
(Doing the final stretches)

2111
01:12:46,166 --> 01:12:47,633
(Thud)

2112
01:12:47,633 --> 01:12:49,152
TRAINEE: It's slippery.

2113
01:12:49,568 --> 01:12:51,166
TRAINEE: Let's try marking the choreography.

2114
01:12:51,166 --> 01:12:52,096
ALL: Yes.

2115
01:12:52,096 --> 01:12:52,704
(Marking: simply matching each other's
movements, positions, and paths)

2116
01:12:52,704 --> 01:12:53,248
TRAINEE: With the music?

2117
01:12:53,248 --> 01:12:53,728
TRAINEE: That's fine though.

2118
01:12:53,728 --> 01:12:54,528
TRAINEE: No, just marking...

2119
01:12:54,528 --> 01:12:55,328
TRAINEE: We'll do the music ourselves.

2120
01:12:55,328 --> 01:12:56,233
TRAINEE: Ah, this is it.

2121
01:12:56,233 --> 01:12:58,633
(Here's the center)
SONGHA: Let's use that black line as the reference.

2122
01:12:58,976 --> 01:13:00,000
(Checking the mirror)
TRAINEE: Wow, it's been a while.

2123
01:13:00,000 --> 01:13:01,800
SONGHA: Please move to the side.

2124
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:02,800
(Round song)
TRAINEE: Please go to the side.

2125
01:13:02,966 --> 01:13:04,066
TRAINEE: Sorry!

2126
01:13:04,366 --> 01:13:08,433
HANBI: Since there are no numbers,
please use the mirror to match.

2127
01:13:08,433 --> 01:13:09,500
(Checking the mirror)

2128
01:13:09,500 --> 01:13:11,066
DANIEL: But KASSHO, I think you need to step out more.

2129
01:13:11,104 --> 01:13:12,544
DANIEL: Hey HAMIN, check them for a second.

2130
01:13:13,632 --> 01:13:15,104
HAMIN: SONGHA should move in a bit.

2131
01:13:15,104 --> 01:13:15,968
(HAMIN adjusting his position slightly as the center)

2132
01:13:15,968 --> 01:13:17,824
TRAINEE: Move out a bit.

2133
01:13:18,048 --> 01:13:18,784
TRAINEE: And...

2134
01:13:18,784 --> 01:13:19,968
HANBI: Alright, let's try.

2135
01:13:20,832 --> 01:13:24,128
(Starting practice in HAMIN's rhythm)
HANBI: Five, six, seven, eight.

2136
01:13:24,384 --> 01:13:27,936
HANBI: One, two, three, four.

2137
01:13:27,936 --> 01:13:31,648
HANBI: Five, six, seven, eight.

2138
01:13:31,648 --> 01:13:32,672
(Everyone buzzing after returning
to practice after a long time)

2139
01:13:32,672 --> 01:13:35,744
HANBI: One, two, three, four.

2140
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:38,816
HANBI: Five, six, seven, eight.

2141
01:13:38,816 --> 01:13:39,552
SONGHA: Ah, it's slippery.

2142
01:13:39,744 --> 01:13:40,480
HANBI: One.

2143
01:13:40,608 --> 01:13:41,248
TATA: It's slippery.

2144
01:13:41,248 --> 01:13:42,240
(Distracted by the slippery floor)
TRAINEE: It's slippery here.

2145
01:13:42,432 --> 01:13:43,232
HYUNJUN: It's slippery.

2146
01:13:44,192 --> 01:13:44,928
TRAINEE: It's really slippery.

2147
01:13:46,176 --> 01:13:46,976
DANIEL: The center's here though.

2148
01:13:46,976 --> 01:13:47,680
HYUNJUN: No, it's over here.

2149
01:13:48,966 --> 01:13:50,900
(Missed the moves while trying to keep the center)

2150
01:13:50,900 --> 01:13:52,736
SONGHA: Wait, wait.
Stop, stop, stop! Let's do it again.

2151
01:13:52,736 --> 01:13:53,440
TRAINEE: Five, six.

2152
01:13:53,568 --> 01:13:54,560
(The center debate continues)
HARUTA: Was the center right in the first place?

2153
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:55,936
WOOLIN: That's not the center.

2154
01:13:56,736 --> 01:13:57,600
(Forgot the choreography in the midst of it)
TRAINEE: What was it?

2155
01:13:57,600 --> 01:13:58,496
TRAINEE: With love.

2156
01:13:58,496 --> 01:13:59,296
(Still looking for the center)

2157
01:13:59,296 --> 01:13:59,840
TRAINEE: Protect

2158
01:14:00,544 --> 01:14:01,696
TRAINEE: me.

2159
01:14:01,920 --> 01:14:02,976
TRAINEE: Together.

2160
01:14:02,976 --> 01:14:04,864
TRAINEE: We need to spread out.

2161
01:14:04,864 --> 01:14:05,600
TRAINEE: Spread out.

2162
01:14:08,766 --> 01:14:09,408
(First practice ends)

2163
01:14:09,408 --> 01:14:10,272
TRAINEE: This foot.

2164
01:14:11,733 --> 01:14:12,224
(Solo ending fairy)

2165
01:14:12,224 --> 01:14:12,896
HANBI: Well,

2166
01:14:13,666 --> 01:14:15,733
HANBI: first of all, what we
need to pay attention to is...

2167
01:14:15,733 --> 01:14:17,700
HANBI: Because there are no numbers on the floor.

2168
01:14:17,700 --> 01:14:18,900
HANBI: It might be a bit
difficult to align symmetrically.

2169
01:14:18,900 --> 01:14:20,320
HANBI: Please, at least align the side rows.

2170
01:14:20,320 --> 01:14:21,024
TRAINEE: Got it.

2171
01:14:21,833 --> 01:14:22,784
(Everyone focusing on the eldest's feedback)

2172
01:14:22,784 --> 01:14:23,808
HANBI: When you go step-step like this...

2173
01:14:24,064 --> 01:14:24,896
HANBI: Right foot.

2174
01:14:25,566 --> 01:14:26,592
(Continuing corrections)
HANBI: Your right foot needs to go forward.

2175
01:14:26,592 --> 01:14:27,520
- TRAINEE: Yes.
- TRAINEE: Okay.

2176
01:14:27,520 --> 01:14:28,600
HANBI: Okay, good.

2177
01:14:28,600 --> 01:14:30,933
HANBI: And when you do this, the hands,
you remember we fixed this before, right?

2178
01:14:30,933 --> 01:14:32,928
HANBI: Some of you are still doing it like this.

2179
01:14:32,928 --> 01:14:33,856
TRAINEE: That's bad.

2180
01:14:33,856 --> 01:14:35,040
HANBI: Yeah, that's bad.

2181
01:14:35,168 --> 01:14:36,672
HANBI: Please make sure to spread this out.

2182
01:14:36,672 --> 01:14:37,300
TRAINEE: Yes.

2183
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:40,960
HANBI: Remember the parts
that didn't go well during marking...

2184
01:14:41,088 --> 01:14:41,600
TRAINEE: Yes.

2185
01:14:42,433 --> 01:14:45,433
(They try again with the music this time)

2186
01:15:00,533 --> 01:15:02,933
(Seems to be going smoothly this time)

2187
01:15:04,733 --> 01:15:05,700
JUSTIN: Why is the music so fast?

2188
01:15:05,733 --> 01:15:07,866
(Taken aback by the fast music this time)
TRAINEE: Exactly.

2189
01:15:08,320 --> 01:15:09,233
(Minor collisions)
TRAINEE: What are you doing?

2190
01:15:09,466 --> 01:15:10,700
HANBI: Focus! Focus!

2191
01:15:11,488 --> 01:15:12,544
(Slip)

2192
01:15:12,544 --> 01:15:13,568
HANBI: What are you doing?

2193
01:15:13,568 --> 01:15:14,784
HANBI: Spread out! Spread out!

2194
01:15:16,100 --> 01:15:18,933
(After finishing the run-through with music...)

2195
01:15:19,232 --> 01:15:20,384
HANBI: Everyone.

2196
01:15:20,900 --> 01:15:23,366
HANBI: I think you forgot a lot
since you haven't practiced lately.

2197
01:15:23,366 --> 01:15:25,500
HANBI: The song sounds fast right now,

2198
01:15:25,500 --> 01:15:28,300
HANBI: but overall we need to calm down
and listen to the music more.

2199
01:15:28,300 --> 01:15:32,066
HANBI: Some people are speeding up their timing,

2200
01:15:32,066 --> 01:15:33,280
HANBI: so stay calmer!

2201
01:15:33,376 --> 01:15:34,048
TRAINEE: Okay.

2202
01:15:34,304 --> 01:15:35,200
DANIEL: Let's go.

2203
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:35,968
(Decided to film it for monitoring)

2204
01:15:36,096 --> 01:15:37,568
HANBI: Please focus as much as possible.

2205
01:15:37,568 --> 01:15:38,496
TRAINEE: Yes.

2206
01:15:42,336 --> 01:15:48,160
(Students seriously try without making mistakes)

2207
01:15:51,904 --> 01:15:53,120
(The song ends)

2208
01:15:55,666 --> 01:15:57,280
(Taking deep breaths)
TRAINEE: Wow, that was intense.

2209
01:15:57,600 --> 01:15:58,336
TRAINEE: That was fast.

2210
01:15:59,233 --> 01:16:00,466
HANBI: Let's watch it.

2211
01:16:00,466 --> 01:16:01,568
HANBI: Alright, everyone, please be quiet.

2212
01:16:01,568 --> 01:16:03,666
(Huddling together to watch the video)

2213
01:16:04,233 --> 01:16:09,066
(Everyone sweating profusely
and focusing on monitoring)

2214
01:16:13,966 --> 01:16:18,833
(Watching without blinking)

2215
01:16:19,700 --> 01:16:22,366
(After the serious monitoring)

2216
01:16:22,366 --> 01:16:26,166
HANBI: The formation mismatch can't really
be helped since there are no floor numbers.

2217
01:16:26,166 --> 01:16:29,100
HANBI: But it seems like everyone
forgot their facial expressions.

2218
01:16:29,100 --> 01:16:31,800
HANBI: I think we need to act a bit more.

2219
01:16:31,800 --> 01:16:33,266
HANBI: We kind of forgot everything.

2220
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,466
HANBI: You know, match
everything perfectly during such moves.

2221
01:16:35,466 --> 01:16:36,700
HANBI: Make the moves bigger,

2222
01:16:36,700 --> 01:16:37,600
HANBI: so it doesn't turn out like this.

2223
01:16:37,600 --> 01:16:39,680
(Add details to each movement)
HANBI: Make it big and precise.

2224
01:16:39,680 --> 01:16:40,448
HANBI: The hand comes.

2225
01:16:40,960 --> 01:16:41,833
HANBI: Movement path.

2226
01:16:41,833 --> 01:16:44,700
HANBI: The timing for each
is a bit different, you know?

2227
01:16:44,700 --> 01:16:47,366
DANIEL: Rather than everything being off,

2228
01:16:47,366 --> 01:16:50,400
DANIEL: it feels like it's slippery,
and we can't focus well?

2229
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:52,933
DANIEL: So just snap into focus...

2230
01:16:52,933 --> 01:16:56,300
DANIEL: and redo expressions and lip-sync.

2231
01:16:56,300 --> 01:17:00,128
DANIEL: Even if it's slippery, stay immersed.

2232
01:17:00,128 --> 01:17:00,933
TRAINEE: Okay.

2233
01:17:00,933 --> 01:17:02,144
HANBI: Let's just make it clean.

2234
01:17:02,144 --> 01:17:03,392
HANBI: And bring out the expressions.

2235
01:17:03,392 --> 01:17:04,608
DANIEL: Immersion! Stay immersed!

2236
01:17:04,608 --> 01:17:05,248
TRAINEE: Immersion.

2237
01:17:05,466 --> 01:17:06,200
TRAINEE: Focus!

2238
01:17:06,528 --> 01:17:07,072
DANIEL: Immersion!

2239
01:17:07,392 --> 01:17:09,088
(Emphasizing focus for reshoot)
TRAINEE: Focus, expressions.

2240
01:17:09,088 --> 01:17:10,880
DANIEL: You! Don't lose focus!

2241
01:17:10,880 --> 01:17:11,840
(Immersion)
DANIEL: You're the one

2242
01:17:12,032 --> 01:17:13,248
DANIEL: who goes like this the most.

2243
01:17:14,112 --> 01:17:15,616
HYUNJUN: I can do it now.
I changed my shoes so I won't slip.

2244
01:17:53,248 --> 01:17:54,400
(Heavy breathing fills the room)

2245
01:17:54,400 --> 01:17:55,520
DANIEL: That's it.

2246
01:17:55,840 --> 01:17:56,768
TRAINEE: Blackout.

2247
01:17:56,768 --> 01:17:57,536
TRAINEE: Electrocution?

2248
01:17:57,536 --> 01:17:58,208
TRAINEE: Electrocution.

2249
01:17:58,432 --> 01:17:58,976
TRAINEE: Electrocution.

2250
01:17:58,976 --> 01:17:59,680
TRAINEE: Electrocution.

2251
01:18:00,133 --> 01:18:01,966
(Checking the recorded video)

2252
01:18:02,368 --> 01:18:02,848
DANIEL: Huh?

2253
01:18:02,848 --> 01:18:03,616
TRAINEE: Let's go back a bit.

2254
01:18:03,616 --> 01:18:04,608
DANIEL: Hey.

2255
01:18:05,152 --> 01:18:05,856
(What's going on?)

2256
01:18:07,232 --> 01:18:08,064
(Collapsed)
TRAINEE: Huh?

2257
01:18:09,024 --> 01:18:11,200
(It powers off just ten seconds after starting)

2258
01:18:11,200 --> 01:18:12,128
JUSTIN: Good work, everyone.

2259
01:18:13,933 --> 01:18:16,166
SONGHA: We can't help it, today's practice is over.

2260
01:18:16,166 --> 01:18:17,900
SONGHA: This is as far as we can go.

2261
01:18:18,466 --> 01:18:19,833
SONGHA: There is no other choice.

2262
01:18:20,833 --> 01:18:24,233
(Moving off to wash up one by one after practice)

2263
01:18:25,120 --> 01:18:28,448
(After playing all day,)

2264
01:18:28,448 --> 01:18:32,200
(still bursting with energy.)

2265
01:18:33,233 --> 01:18:38,400
(Students writing picture diaries
in their preferred spaces)

2266
01:18:39,433 --> 01:18:41,568
(CHARLIE: I was so curious and excited
because of the sudden news about the picnic!)

2267
01:18:41,568 --> 01:18:43,936
(KACHIN: We went to the beach and saw the sunset,
and both the sea and the sky were incredibly beautiful)

2268
01:18:51,466 --> 01:18:55,500
(HYUNJUN: Going with friends was nostalgic,
with fun and happiness magnified five times)

2269
01:18:55,616 --> 01:18:57,400
(A one-day school field trip!)

2270
01:18:57,400 --> 01:19:02,900
(JUSTIN: No matter how old I get,
I hope this memory stays with me)

2271
01:19:04,480 --> 01:19:07,900
(HANBI: We engraved our dreams once again)

2272
01:19:07,900 --> 01:19:13,266
(and made unforgettable memories)

2273
01:19:15,072 --> 01:19:19,552
(SONGHA: Let's do our best tomorrow as well, goodbye)

2274
01:19:19,712 --> 01:19:20,256
(Next Episode Preview)

2275
01:19:20,256 --> 01:19:22,240
(When night falls on the school,)

2276
01:19:22,733 --> 01:19:24,966
(the school becomes a completely different space)

2277
01:19:25,472 --> 01:19:28,566
(What happened at the school that night?)

2278
01:19:28,864 --> 01:19:30,433
JUSTIN: At this moment,

2279
01:19:30,433 --> 01:19:32,666
JUSTIN: I might forget that I'm older than him.

2280
01:19:33,056 --> 01:19:36,700
(CHOI DAEWON, a student who attended)

2281
01:19:36,700 --> 01:19:38,100
(school with you,)

2282
01:19:38,100 --> 01:19:39,800
(has gone missing)

2283
01:19:40,288 --> 01:19:43,776
(Someone was with us at the school)

2284
01:19:44,766 --> 01:19:48,266
(The time we spent happily, unaware of anything)

2285
01:19:48,800 --> 01:19:49,856
TRAINEE: KYUHYUN once told us

2286
01:19:51,008 --> 01:19:52,352
TRAINEE: when someone gives you something delicious,

2287
01:19:52,608 --> 01:19:53,280
TRAINEE: always be suspicious.

2288
01:19:54,300 --> 01:19:54,784
(Night rules)

2289
01:19:54,784 --> 01:19:56,736
(Today's menu)

2290
01:19:56,736 --> 01:19:58,400
(Horror Experience)

2291
01:19:58,966 --> 01:20:02,233
(1. If you see someone, ignore them.)

2292
01:20:02,666 --> 01:20:04,633
(2. If you spot student XX,)

2293
01:20:05,133 --> 01:20:07,200
(evacuate to a safe restroom)

2294
01:20:07,700 --> 01:20:10,300
(The staff will come to rescue you)

2295
01:20:10,866 --> 01:20:12,800
(4. The restroom is a safe place)

2296
01:20:13,200 --> 01:20:14,900
(5. If you find the third stall in the restroom...)
HARUTA: Is it here?

2297
01:20:15,333 --> 01:20:18,033
(6. Come out immediately)

2298
01:20:19,100 --> 01:20:20,933
WOOLIN: You said it was safe...

2299
01:20:22,500 --> 01:20:25,333
(9. The staff will not follow you)

2300
01:20:26,033 --> 01:20:26,624
(10. If you're alone, cover your ears from something)

2301
01:20:26,720 --> 01:20:29,056
TRAINEE: We have to cover the ears. Cover the ears.

2302
01:20:31,533 --> 01:20:33,533
HYUNJUN: But what if I don't understand this?

2303
01:20:33,568 --> 01:20:34,176
TRAINEE: Let's take it with us.

2304
01:20:34,176 --> 01:20:38,400
(You'll understand in the next episode)

2305
01:20:38,784 --> 01:20:40,960
(The closing song 'Shine' – PENTAGON)

2306
01:20:41,024 --> 01:20:41,408
JUSTIN: Okay.

2307
01:20:41,536 --> 01:20:43,488
KACHIN: One, two, three.

2308
01:20:44,480 --> 01:20:45,184
STAFF: One, two.

2309
01:20:45,472 --> 01:20:46,016
- SONGHA: Three.
- SADAHARU: Okay.

2310
01:20:47,552 --> 01:20:48,480
JAEWON: Make the best-looking face.

2311
01:20:48,640 --> 01:20:50,528
JAEWON: Make sure no one looks bad, no exceptions!

2312
01:20:51,264 --> 01:20:52,000
